INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2019-01-09 20:57:48','2019-01-09 20:57:48','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start writing!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Hello world!','','trash','open','open','','hello-world__trashed','','','2019-01-09 21:08:07','2019-01-09 21:08:07','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2019-01-09 20:57:48','2019-01-09 20:57:48','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>...or something like this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Sample Page','','trash','closed','open','','sample-page__trashed','','','2019-01-09 21:43:26','2019-01-09 21:43:26','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(3,1,'2019-01-09 20:57:48','2019-01-09 20:57:48','<!-- wp:heading --><h2>Who we are</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>Our website address is: http://localhost/robby-fresh.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>What personal data we collect and why we collect it</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Comments</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor&#8217;s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Media</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Contact forms</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Cookies</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you have an account and you log in to this site, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select &quot;Remember Me&quot;, your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Embedded content from other websites</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Analytics</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Who we share your data with</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>How long we retain your data</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>What rights you have over your data</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Where we send your data</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Your contact information</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Additional information</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>How we protect your data</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>What data breach procedures we have in place</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>What third parties we receive data from</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>What automated decision making and/or profiling we do with user data</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Industry regulatory disclosure requirements</h3><!-- /wp:heading -->','Privacy Policy','','trash','closed','open','','privacy-policy__trashed','','','2019-01-09 21:43:26','2019-01-09 21:43:26','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/?page_id=3',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2019-01-09 20:57:59','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2019-01-09 20:57:59','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/?p=4',0,'post','',0),(5,1,'2019-01-09 21:01:41','2019-01-09 21:01:41','','Default','','publish','closed','closed','','default','','','2019-01-09 21:01:41','2019-01-09 21:01:41','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/2019/01/09/default/',0,'advgb_profiles','',0),(12,1,'2015-10-19 05:06:16','2015-10-19 05:06:16','<!-- wp:fl-builder/layout -->\n	<p>Hi! My name is Robby. Welcome to my blog.</p>\n<p>I am former freelance web developer &amp; designer turned marketer/entrepreneur. I am one of the co-founders of Beaver Builder, a <a href=\"https://www.wpbeaverbuilder.com\">website builder for WordPress</a>.</p>\n<h2>Lets Connect</h2>\n<p>I go through spurts of activity on social media and I love connecting with people.</p>\n<p>Find me on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mybbor\">Facebook</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/robbymccullough\">Twitter</a>, or <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/robbymccullough/\">Instagram</a>.</p>\n<h2>About my Blog</h2>\n<p>One of the reasons I decided to start a blog was to share some of the stories and lessons I\'ve learned in starting a company. I\'ve been inspired by the transparency of many great companies in our space and, in a way, I see this as a chance to give back—to share some knowledge.</p>\n<p>Here are a few of the things I am hoping to write about:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Music / Concerts</li>\n<li>Food / Cooking</li>\n<li>Coffee</li>\n<li>Traveling</li>\n<li>Business</li>\n<li>Marketing</li>\n<li>Productivity</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Tools and Software</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WordPress</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.wpbeaverbuilder.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Beaver Builder</a> (of course)</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough//go/godaddy-manged-wordpress\">GoDaddy Managed WordPress Hosting</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:fl-builder/layout -->','About Robby McCullough','','trash','closed','closed','','about__trashed','','','2019-01-09 21:43:26','2019-01-09 21:43:26','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?page_id=12',0,'page','',0),(75,1,'2016-03-14 05:35:51','2016-03-14 05:35:51','','Robby McCullough - Ramblings on Business, WordPress, & Life','','trash','closed','closed','','robby-mccullough-ramblings-on-business-wordpress-life__trashed','','','2019-01-09 21:43:26','2019-01-09 21:43:26','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?page_id=75',0,'page','',0),(91,1,'2016-04-09 07:30:45','2016-04-09 07:30:45','<h2>Have you ever looked through a telescope?</h2>\nMy dad always had a&nbsp;telescope in our garage.\n\nIt wasn\'t the cliche, long and skinny refractor telescope, but a hefty 10 inch <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dobsonian_telescope\" target=\"_blank\">Dobsonian telescope</a>.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_108\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"340\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/dobsonian-telescope.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-108\"><img class=\"wp-image-108\" src=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough//wp-content/uploads/2016/04/dobsonian-telescope-300x190.jpg\" alt=\"dobsonian-telescope\" width=\"340\" height=\"216\"></a> Yeah, kinda like that &#x1f446;&#x1f3fc;[/caption]\n\nOn a whim one day, I decided I wanted to play around with my Dad\'s telescope.&nbsp;I don\'t know why. It sat for years untouched and I saw it every day. But on this&nbsp;particular day, I had an urge. And on that evening, I dusted off the cobwebs and brought it out into the evening.\n\nThat was the beginning of an obsession—an&nbsp;<em>addiction&nbsp;</em>even.\n\nI fell in love with the stars. I spent my days looking at weather reports, studying star maps, scouting planet trajectories, nebulae, and star clusters.\n\n<a href=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough//go/ dobsonian-telescope\" target=\"_blank\">This book</a> on building large aperture telescopes sat, untouched, on our family bookshelf for years. Of course, I dug it out and read it cover to cover multiple times.\n\nOne of the sentiments from that book&nbsp;that I\'ll never forget is, at some point, everyone who completes a telescope build has to make the transition from telescope builder to a telescope user. It\'s so easy to get wrapped up in the fun and excitement of building your own telescope, one forgets the original goal: to look at the stars.\n\n[bctt tweet=\"Transitioning from builder to user is a bittersweet milestone of many DIY projects.\"]\n\nWell, that\'s how I feel today. I\'ve spent the last several weeks designing and building my blog here, and today, I am going from blog builder to writer.\n<h2>Welcome to RobbyMcCullough.com</h2>\nIf you\'re reading this, thanks for being here!\n\nI\'ve had the opportunity to do some writing &nbsp;on the <a href=\"https://www.wpbeaverbuilder.com/blog/\" target=\"_blank\">Beaver Builder Blog</a> and it\'s been a blast. I keep a <a href=\"https://trello.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Trello</a> list of article ideas, and some of them are just too personal or off-topic from what would work for there. That\'s what this blog is for.\n\nI covered a bit of this on my <a href=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough//about/\">about page</a>, but I\'ve been inspired by many of the bloggers in the WordPress business space. I\'m hoping this blog is my opportunity to give back a bit and share what I\'ve learned over the past two years since we started&nbsp;Beaver Builder.\n\nFull disclosure: I\'m also hoping to do some experiments with affiliate marketing. There\'s likely to be a smattering of affiliate links when applicable. I certainly don\'t want to be dodgy about it, but why not try to bring in a bit of extra cash, right?\n<h2>What Software/Tools am I Using?</h2>\nGreat question. Well,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.wpbeaverbuilder.com\" target=\"_blank\">Beaver Builder</a> of course!\n\nFor the nitty-gritty breakdown, check out my <a href=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough//about/\">About Page</a>. I\'m planning to keep an updated list of all the WordPress plugins I am running, and I also have a link to a GitHub repo with the Beaver Builder Child Theme configuration I\'m using. I\'ve done a fair deal of work customizing the Beaver Builder Theme to make it a badass personal blog, so feel free to take what I \'ve done and run with it.\n\n[bctt tweet=\"Check out @RobbyMcCullough\'s @BeaverBuilder Child Theme configuration on Github. http://bit.ly/1qml3gZ\" via=\"no\" url=\"no\"]\n<h2>In Closing</h2>\nWell, that about sums it up.\n\nIf you\'re interested to see what I am going to write next, you can subscribe to my blog using the form below.\n\nIf you\'re feeling social,&nbsp;<em>please</em> say hello in the comments section! Until next time. :)','A Blog is Born - Transitioning from Builder to User','Welcome to my blog. This is the first (hopefully of many) blog post and marks my transition of going from a blog builder to a writer.','trash','open','open','','a-blog-is-born-transitioning-from-builder-to-user__trashed','','','2016-04-09 07:30:45','2016-04-09 07:30:45','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=91',0,'post','',0),(108,1,'2016-04-09 21:04:08','2016-04-09 21:04:08','','dobsonian-telescope','','inherit','open','closed','','dobsonian-telescope','','','2016-04-09 21:04:08','2016-04-09 21:04:08','',91,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/dobsonian-telescope.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(147,1,'2016-04-17 16:24:49','2016-04-17 16:24:49','','headshot','','inherit','open','closed','','headshot','','','2016-04-17 16:24:49','2016-04-17 16:24:49','',12,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/headshot.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(175,1,'2016-04-17 23:29:34','2016-04-17 23:29:34','','astrophotography','','inherit','open','closed','','astrophotography','','','2016-04-17 23:29:34','2016-04-17 23:29:34','',91,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/astrophotography.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(179,1,'2016-05-16 00:43:37','2016-05-16 00:43:37','<h2>Cooking&nbsp;is a pain—but it doesn\'t have to be.</h2>\nLike many, I was a fast food and take out guy for the first few decades of my life. Super burritos, frozen corndogs, instant oatmeal, you name it; that\'s what I survived on.\n\nCooking is hard. Let\'s face it. Compared to take out or fast food, it\'s a real pain—especially if you\'re just cooking for one. Quality ingredients aren\'t cheap. Navigating a grocery store is daunting. And after all that time and effort getting ingredients, messing up a recipe or burning a piece of meat is a glaring example of your failure and feels so wasteful.\n<h3>Say Hello SunBasket</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" style=\"float: left; background: #FFF; border: 0; border-radius: 3px; box-shadow: 0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; margin-right: 40px; max-width: 400px; padding: 0; width: calc(100% - 2px);\" data-instgrm-version=\"6\">\n<div style=\"padding: 8px;\">\n<div style=\"background: #F8F8F8; line-height: 0; margin-top: 40px; padding: 50.0% 0; text-align: center; width: 100%;\"></div>\n<p style=\"color: #c9c8cd; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px; margin-bottom: 0; margin-top: 8px; overflow: hidden; padding: 8px 0 7px; text-align: center; text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap;\"><a style=\"color: #c9c8cd; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 17px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/BDw3Ye1uBa2/\" target=\"_blank\">A photo posted by Robby McCullough (@robbymccullough)</a> on <time style=\"font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px;\" datetime=\"2016-04-04T03:37:55+00:00\">Apr 3, 2016 at 8:37pm PDT</time></p>\n\n</div></blockquote>\n<script src=\"//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js\" async=\"\" defer=\"defer\"></script>\n\nA few months ago, I was introduced to a food-to-doorstep service called <a href=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough//go/sunbasket\" target=\"_blank\">SunBasket</a>. The whole idea is they send pre-measured ingredients and easy-to-follow recipes right to your doorstep. It\'s brilliant!\n\nYou can choose how many meals a week you want and how many people you\'re cooking for. SunBasket\'s award winning chef will curate and prepare all the goodies you need and they\'ll ship it right to your doorstep. The recipes are easy enough to follow and&nbsp;while I am not a picky eater, every meal I\'ve made has been delicious.&nbsp;\n<h3>Cooking is All About Pairing</h3>\nFlavor pairings are one of the fundamental aspects of cooking. Certain things just mesh well together.\n\n<img class=\"alignright wp-image-242 size-medium\" src=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough//wp-content/uploads/2016/05/51-pQeLTeCL-253x300.jpg\" alt=\"51-pQeLTeCL\" width=\"253\" height=\"300\">\n\nNot long after I started up with SunBasket, I was chatting with a friend about it over lunch and he suggested a great book, <a href=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough//go/four-hour-chef\" target=\"_blank\"><em>The Four Hour Chef</em></a> by Tim Ferriss.\n\n<em>The Four Hour Chef</em> is a book about learning and it uses food as the medium. It teaches you how to learn complex subjects by breaking them down and focusing on the aspects that give you the best ROI on time invested.\n\nSunBasket provides the hands-on experience while the book covers the how and the why. Why certain flavors go well together and the origins the flavor profiles originate from. How to progressively equip a kitchen. Why you should use a meat thermometer. How to&nbsp;<em>learn</em> knife skills.\n\nThe book is the lecture and SunBasket is the hands-on lab.\n<h2>Tools of the Trade</h2>\nLike any other activity, there\'s a thriving industry working to convince you of all the things you&nbsp;<em>need</em> to cook. Juicers, emulsifiers, blenders, peelers, de-stemmers, spices, oils, pots, pans. It\'s daunting and expensive to try to keep up.\n\nThis is one of the things I love about The Four Hour Chef. One of the key lessons in the book is how to slowly stock up a functional kitchen. The lessons and meals are broken up in a way that you can start with a minimal amount of gear, then add the required pieces as you work through the book.\n\nI\'ve done a little bit of grilling, and I\'ve cooked up a few meals here and there, so I had a lot of the gear already. To be honest, I like gear. I enjoy shopping and I am a bit of an Amazon Prime junkie, so I\'ve probably gone a bit overboard in the gear department. That said, there\'s a small list of essentials that will make your cooking experience much more enjoyable. I thought I was cursed with the inability to ever cook an omelet until I got a halfway decent non-stick cooking pan. The difference was night and day. The only thing standing between me and a proper egg dish was my pan.\n<h3>The Essentials</h3>\nOkay, this is the bare bones list of things to get started with SunBasket. If you\'re going to go with the Four Hour Chef route, disregard this list and follow the author\'s suggestions in the book instead.\n<h4>Chef\'s Knife</h4>\nLastly, be sure to pick up a sharpening steel and <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SBn1i9YqN1k\" target=\"_blank\">learn how to use it</a>.\n<h4>Cutting Board</h4>\n<h4>Sauce Pot</h4>\n<h4>Olive Oil</h4>\n<h4>Medium Pan</h4>\n<h4>Salt and Pepper</h4>\n<h3>The Niceties</h3>\n<h4>Kitchen Towels</h4>\n<h4>Auto Grinders</h4>\n<h4>Grater</h4>\n<h4>Peeler</h4>\n<h4>Garlic Press</h4>\nTimer or Alexa\n\nVege Scrubber\n<h4>Meat Thermometer</h4>\nThat\'s another barrier to entry for cooking: pots, pans, knives, spices, cutting boards, spatulas. You need a lot of stuff!\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" style=\"background: #FFF; border: 0; border-radius: 3px; box-shadow: 0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width: 400px; padding: 0; width: calc(100% - 2px);\" data-instgrm-version=\"7\">\n<div style=\"padding: 8px;\">\n<div style=\"background: #F8F8F8; line-height: 0; margin-top: 40px; padding: 50.0% 0; text-align: center; width: 100%;\"></div>\n<a style=\"color: #c9c8cd; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 17px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/BFW6xopOBeG/\" target=\"_blank\">A photo posted by Robby McCullough (@robbymccullough)</a> on <time style=\"font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px;\" datetime=\"2016-05-13T18:50:06+00:00\">May 13, 2016 at 11:50am PDT</time>\n\n</div></blockquote>\n<script src=\"//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js\" async=\"\" defer=\"defer\"></script>\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" style=\"float: right; background: #FFF; border: 0; border-radius: 3px; box-shadow: 0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; margin-left: 40px; max-width: 400px; padding: 0; width: calc(100% - 2px);\" data-instgrm-version=\"6\">\n<div style=\"padding: 8px;\">\n<div style=\"background: #F8F8F8; line-height: 0; margin-top: 40px; padding: 50.0% 0; text-align: center; width: 100%;\"></div>\n<a style=\"color: #c9c8cd; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 17px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/BEFNEUAuBaO/\" target=\"_blank\">A photo posted by Robby McCullough (@robbymccullough)</a> on <time style=\"font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px;\" datetime=\"2016-04-12T01:12:13+00:00\">Apr 11, 2016 at 6:12pm PDT</time>\n\n</div></blockquote>\n<script src=\"//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js\" async=\"\" defer=\"defer\"></script>','From Take-Out Champion to Sunbasket Gourmet','Talking food, cooking, and SunBasket. I\'ve been cooking a lot recently thanks to a service called SunBasket and the Four Hour Chef book by Tim Ferriss.','trash','open','open','','from-take-out-to-sunbasket-gourmet__trashed','','','2016-05-16 00:43:37','2016-05-16 00:43:37','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=179',0,'post','',0),(184,1,'2016-04-20 06:47:25','2016-04-20 06:47:25','','sunbasket','','inherit','open','closed','','sunbasket','','','2016-04-20 06:47:25','2016-04-20 06:47:25','',91,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/sunbasket.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(200,1,'2016-04-29 04:12:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00','I just spent the last three days at Collision Conference in New Orleans. It was a great experience and, sitting here reflecting after all is said and done, I have\n<h2>Stand Out</h2>\nWhen I was 15, I grew dreadlocks and wore tie-dye shirts and dashikis. My goal wasn\'t to draw attention to myself; it was an unavoidable side effect. For better or worse, I quickly learned what it felt like to walk into a room and command everyone\'s attention.\n\nThese days, I still wear my hair long and I love wearing bright colors. I draw no where near as much attention as when I was a teenager, but I think I stand out in a crowd. The way I present myself isn\'t to draw attention, it\'s just the way I am, but there is value in standing out from the crowd. Be yourself, but feel free to explore the more extreme visual/fashion sides of yourself that will set you apart from everyone else in the room. When you hear the names Dennis Rodman and Larry Bird, which one sticks in your mind. Which face do you remember?\n<h2>You Don\'t have to Fit in to be Presentable</h2>\nI always fall into this trap. If I am going to an event, I\'ll bring all my collar shirts and slacks to the dry cleaner or buy a new \"nice\" outfit. Then, I\'ll get there and see one guy wearing shorts or a tshirt, and that will be my anchor.\n<h2>Wear What Makes You Comfortable</h2>\nI\'m just not comfortable in formal/corporate attire, so I don\'t wear it. Instead, I\'ll go out of my way to make sure I have a nice, clean, new pair of jeans or a nice, new, clean pair of tennis shoes. I\'ll shave and get a hair cut and go to great lengths to make myself look presentable and professional, <em>without</em> wearing a suit and tie.\n<h2>Take Advantage of \'Meeting Moments\'</h2>\n&nbsp;\n\nAt any conference, you\'re going to have a finite number of perfect \"meeting moments.\" Take advantage of them!\n\nLines are a great example. At collision conference, it seemed like everyone was clamoring to meet investors. When I was standing in the lunch line, I said, \"this was the longest line yesterday and it\'s the shortest today. Good deal.\" That kicked off a conversation with a woman I later found out was a partner at a prominent investment firm.\n\nWhen I was walking back to my Airbnb, there was a guy a few paces ahead that was wearing a conference name tag and wristband. At the next traffic stop, I said something along the lines of, \"Hey, you were at the conference, too?\"\n\nThe guy I met happened to be a local, and as we chatted on our wal home, we agreed to meet up an hour or so later and take an Airbnb to the after party. He introduced me to more people than I could count on two hands that evening.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWork the Eye Contact\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2>Respect the Ebb and Flow and People\'s Time</h2>\nLearn to Exit a Conversation\n\n&nbsp;\nPut yourself in uncomfortable situations\nDon\'t be afraid to step back and recharge\nBusiness Cards are Lame','How to \'Conference\' Like a Pro','','draft','open','open','','conference-like-pri','','','2016-04-29 04:12:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=200',0,'post','',0),(202,1,'2018-12-14 00:36:15','2018-12-14 00:36:15','Forgive the foreboding title. At my company, Beaver Builder, we\'ve been using bbPress for our support forum for over two years. We recently decided to phase out our support forums for a dedicated ticketing system, HelpScout.\n\nWhen we were starting our plugin business, there were thousands of task on our todo list. Writing the code, finding users, testing our idea, setting up an eCommerce system, setting up an update system, building our website, writing documentation, etc. The list seemed never ending. Amongst those tasks was creating a support system for our users.\n\nWe did some research and found this tutorial by Pippin Williamson on how to setup bbPress as a support forum.\n\nIt looks bad when abandon tickets aren\'t resolved\nPage loads eat up a LOT of time (and money)\nEmail subscriptions and notifications\nTeam management features and statistics\nProne to insecure practices\nNo eCommerce Integration\n\nPros\n\nIntegrates with existing account system\nGroup discussions and community\nSearchable Answers','Considering Using bbPress as a Support Forum? Don\'t!','','trash','open','open','','considering-using-bbpress-support-forum-dont__trashed','','','2018-12-14 00:36:15','2018-12-14 00:36:15','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=202',0,'post','',0),(242,1,'2016-05-22 23:50:38','2016-05-22 23:50:38','','51-pQeLTeCL','','inherit','open','closed','','51-pqeltecl','','','2016-05-22 23:50:38','2016-05-22 23:50:38','',179,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/51-pQeLTeCL.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(249,1,'2018-12-14 00:26:16','2018-12-14 00:26:16','','Tech is art. It\'s beautiful. And it\'s thriving in the Bay Area.','','trash','open','open','','__trashed','','','2018-12-14 00:26:16','2018-12-14 00:26:16','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=249',0,'post','',0),(251,1,'2017-12-27 00:53:29','2017-12-27 00:53:29','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is a really powerful commentary on social media making rounds recently. The rumblings go deeper than this one man and this one video. As an avid social media user, I think it\'s important to realize and understand this idea of \"dopamine driven feedback loops\" and both their power and their danger.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=78oMjNCAayQ\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=78oMjNCAayQ\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I might be breaking my own rule here by posting this, but my hope is that if you dig around a bit there\'s a positive message in here despite the negative subject matter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"My solution\" to the ideas brought up in this video—which I think many of us have felt without being able to articulate as well—is to post positivity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you share things on social media, you\'re putting energy out into the world that people <em>are going to have a reaction to</em>. I try to avoid airing grievances on Facebook. I try to avoid polarizing political and social commentary. I try to avoid sharing things that make me feel good at the expense of someone else.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s go back to the good \'ole days when we shared cat pictures and smiling faces. Post positivity. Bring the Golden Rule back to social media.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Share things that will make others feel good. Make people laugh. Rekindle old connections. Share your vulnerabilities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s up to us, the power users, the influencers, the millennials that championed these platforms and digital lifestyles, to make a difference.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My new year\'s resolution is to share more, share positivity, and share deeper than just the picture-perfect moments. Life is full of peaks and valleys and only sharing at the top paints an unrealistic picture. I want to share the challenges and imperfections too. I want to use social media as a platform to help and improve other\'s lives as opposed to being a crutch for <em>my</em> insecurities and imperfections.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We\'ll see how that goes. Happy New Year and much love to all of you now, in 2018, and forever. :) &#x2764;&#xfe0f;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My New Year\'s Resolution for 2018','','publish','open','open','','my-new-years-resolution-for-2018','','','2017-12-27 00:53:29','2017-12-27 00:53:29','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=251',0,'post','',0),(260,1,'2017-12-26 19:14:31','2017-12-26 19:14:31','','san-francisco-new-years','','inherit','open','closed','','san-francisco-new-years','','','2017-12-26 19:14:31','2017-12-26 19:14:31','',251,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/san-francisco-new-years.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(263,1,'2018-01-12 16:59:04','2018-01-12 16:59:04','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I love reading and learning. I am a voracious reader, but I very rarely read books. My reading material almost entirely consisted of web articles and blog posts. I was turned on to a book called&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Influence-Psychology-Persuasion-Robert-Cialdini/dp/006124189X\"><em>Influence: The Psychology of Persuasion</em></a> and I <em>really</em> wanted to read it. Although, this has happened several times before. I buy the kindle&nbsp;version of the book, then sits there and sits there collecting digital dust.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here\'s a trick that worked for me. I moved all of the social media apps on my phone to a folder hidden on the back page of my phone. I moved the Kindle app front and center and started popping it open and reading a few pages when I otherwise would have popped open my RSS reader, Reddit, Hacker News, Facebook, or Instagram.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Then, I dug up my old Kindle reader and threw it in my car. I have dual USB car charger, so I grabbed a mini-USB cable and started plugging it in and storing it in the car full time. Now, when I am going out anywhere with a wait, or to a restaurant or bar where I normally knock out a lot of my reading (yeah,&nbsp;yeah, I am the guy that reads at the bar..only <em>sometimes</em>), I bring the Kindle along.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So far, it\'s working! I\'ve read more pages from <em>actual</em> books than I have in years!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How I tricked myself into reading more books','','publish','open','open','','how-i-tricked-myself-into-reading-more-books','','','2018-01-12 16:59:04','2018-01-12 16:59:04','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=263',0,'post','',2),(267,1,'2018-01-12 16:58:13','2018-01-12 16:58:13','','read-more-books','','inherit','open','closed','','read-more-books','','','2018-01-12 16:58:13','2018-01-12 16:58:13','',263,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/read-more-books.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(272,1,'2018-12-14 00:27:07','2018-12-14 00:27:07','Gaming and companies both require high-performance teams.\n\nWorking with difficult personalities.\n\nWorking remotely.\n\nSharing the rewards and of hard work.\n\nConsistency and working at something over a long period\n\nDailies. Weeklies.\n\nEasier because the goals are clear and the consequences are mute.','How World of Warcraft trained me to be a successful entrepreneur.','','trash','open','open','','__trashed-2','','','2018-12-14 00:27:07','2018-12-14 00:27:07','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=272',0,'post','',0),(274,1,'2018-01-22 07:14:31','2018-01-22 07:14:31','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YqiiKEmINuQ\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YqiiKEmINuQ\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I started off 2018 with a couple of posts on the blog here, but I am also making an effort to start working more with video. I made a two-part vlog about my trip to Denver as an effort to learn about filming and editing. I just finished up the edit on part 2 and I am having so much fun!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I don\'t know if I\'ll keep posting the vlogs on the blog, but I do like owning my distribution channel and would much prefer to use WordPress as a hub vs. YouTube.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','My First Vlog - Travels hacks from my trip to Denver, CO','','publish','open','open','','my-first-vlog-travels-hacks-from-my-trip-to-denver-co','','','2018-01-22 07:14:31','2018-01-22 07:14:31','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=274',0,'post','',0),(278,1,'2018-01-29 07:13:21','2018-01-29 07:13:21','','denver-part1-featured-image','','inherit','open','closed','','denver-part1-featured-image','','','2018-01-29 07:13:21','2018-01-29 07:13:21','',274,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/denver-part1-featured-image.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(280,1,'2018-02-13 03:08:07','2018-02-13 03:08:07','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c_3hoFxy5f8\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c_3hoFxy5f8\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks a ton @ Scott Pemberton for the tunes. Check out his channel, I guarantee you\'ve <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCZWmU0FSV9eusYi71qfw9Nw\">never seen anyone play the guitar like this</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Happy Valentine\'s Day!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This week, I had an idea all planned out and scrapped it a few days in and decided to go snowboarding instead.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I dabbled with some stop motion animation. I spent 4 days trying to get a timelapse of a flower blooming. I went to the dentist and, maybe as a subconscious act of rebellion, I ate way too many Valentine\'s heart candies. Enjoy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Snowboarding, Love Stories, and Lake Tahoe','','publish','open','open','','snowboarding-love-stories-and-lake-tahoe','','','2018-02-13 03:08:07','2018-02-13 03:08:07','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=280',0,'post','',1),(285,1,'2018-02-13 04:41:18','2018-02-13 04:41:18','','Snowboarding-love-stories-tahoe-final','','inherit','open','closed','','snowboarding-love-stories-tahoe-final','','','2018-02-13 04:41:18','2018-02-13 04:41:18','',280,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Snowboarding-love-stories-tahoe-final.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(288,1,'2018-01-29 04:18:02','2018-01-29 04:18:02','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5L20-ldneBw\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5L20-ldneBw\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Part 2 of my Denver travel vlog. I had so much fun editing this, but I realized all the things I could have done better when filming. Super fun stuff, though. More to come for sure!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Music by:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>• <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/artist/19lQ2rJLlP71FOKESiMNJT\">Ripe</a><a class=\"yt-simple-endpoint style-scope yt-formatted-string\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/redirect?event=video_description&amp;v=5L20-ldneBw&amp;q=https%3A%2F%2Fopen.spotify.com%2Fartist%2F19lQ2rJLlP71FOKESiMNJT&amp;redir_token=pD-j13-8e6vJSwdiA6G2sARsusN8MTUxODY2ODA3N0AxNTE4NTgxNjc3\"><br></a>• A random creative commons snow song<br> • A dude jamming on the street</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','First time EVER seeing it SNOW - Finding Your Style','','publish','open','open','','first-time-ever-seeing-it-snow-finding-your-style','','','2018-01-29 04:18:02','2018-01-29 04:18:02','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=288',0,'post','',0),(291,1,'2018-02-14 04:38:01','2018-02-14 04:38:01','','denver-part-2','','inherit','open','closed','','denver-part-2','','','2018-02-14 04:38:01','2018-02-14 04:38:01','',288,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/denver-part-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(292,1,'2018-02-05 04:38:11','2018-02-05 04:38:11','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y7eIKXMUye8\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y7eIKXMUye8\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I am back at home this week and doing my best to keep the vlog going. I filmed the lunar eclipse and, of course, had to feature Pink Floyd on the tunes for a spacey, psychedelic moon-inspired vlog... Also celebrated my Mom\'s birthday at an almost-too-fancy restaurant. Good times!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Manresa & the Supermoon Eclipse','','publish','open','open','','manresa-the-supermoon-eclipse','','','2018-02-05 04:38:11','2018-02-05 04:38:11','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=292',0,'post','',0),(297,1,'2018-02-14 04:45:42','2018-02-14 04:45:42','','supermoon-eclipse','','inherit','open','closed','','supermoon-eclipse','','','2018-02-14 04:45:42','2018-02-14 04:45:42','',292,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/supermoon-eclipse.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(301,1,'2018-02-20 04:08:00','2018-02-20 04:08:00','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ms9CeRJuRwg\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ms9CeRJuRwg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Music by <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCZWmU0FSV9eusYi71qfw9Nw\">Scott Pemberton</a>.<br>\nThe star of the show:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.wpbeaverbuilder.com/good-old-fashioned-update-post/\">our update post</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This week, I dug into the story of what I do for work and why I love it! I tell the story about how Beaver Builder started and why I am passionate about free, open-source software and WordPress. One thing I didn\'t explain well is that \"free\" as in software is not the same as \"free\" as in beer. The code free, but we still sell access to our software and support.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This a behind-the-scenes look at my day of publishing an update blog post and newsletter. I later found out I totally screwed up the email settings and about 50% of all the emails wound up in people\'s spam folders. Oh well. Live and learn. :) Until next week...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','What I Do for Work','','publish','open','open','','what-i-do','','','2018-02-20 04:08:00','2018-02-20 04:08:00','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=301',0,'post','',0),(316,1,'2018-02-20 04:28:11','2018-02-20 04:28:11','','what-i-do-thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','what-i-do-thumb','','','2018-02-20 04:28:11','2018-02-20 04:28:11','',301,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/what-i-do-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(317,1,'2018-02-20 04:28:26','2018-02-20 04:28:26','http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/cropped-what-i-do-thumb.jpg','cropped-what-i-do-thumb.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-what-i-do-thumb-jpg','','','2018-02-20 04:28:26','2018-02-20 04:28:26','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/cropped-what-i-do-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(318,1,'2018-02-20 04:28:41','2018-02-20 04:28:41','','what-I-do-tiedie-beaver','','inherit','open','closed','','what-i-do-tiedie-beaver','','','2018-02-20 04:28:41','2018-02-20 04:28:41','',301,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/what-I-do-tiedie-beaver.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(320,1,'2018-02-26 23:16:48','2018-02-26 23:16:48','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/Mr7jjPfD53Y\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/Mr7jjPfD53Y\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This week, I did the San Jose Bike Party, fixed my internet, and played tourist in (almost) my own town with a photo/hyperlapse mission to Monterey, CA.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Honorable mentions to State of Mind Public House &amp; Pizzeria, Essential Spirits Alambic Distilleries, and The Entrepreneur’s Guide to Keeping Your Sh*t Together (grab <a href=\"http://amzn.to/2GIETvV\">your copy here</a>).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I am on a mission to reduce the camera shake! Ugh. It\'s so frustrating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Music by...<br><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCZWmU0FSV9eusYi71qfw9Nw\">Scott Pemberton</a>&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCdc607mtldpUdKO7ME49f5Q\">Ripe</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','San Jose Bike Party & Monterey CA Hyperlapses','','publish','open','open','','san-jose-bike-party-monterey-ca-hyperlapses','','','2018-02-26 23:16:48','2018-02-26 23:16:48','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=320',0,'post','',0),(323,1,'2018-02-26 23:10:57','2018-02-26 23:10:57','','san-jose-bike-party-dark','','inherit','open','closed','','san-jose-bike-party-dark','','','2018-02-26 23:10:57','2018-02-26 23:10:57','',320,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/san-jose-bike-party-dark.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(324,1,'2018-02-26 23:11:46','2018-02-26 23:11:46','','thumb-2','','inherit','open','closed','','thumb-2','','','2018-02-26 23:11:46','2018-02-26 23:11:46','',320,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/thumb-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(325,1,'2018-02-26 23:11:57','2018-02-26 23:11:57','http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/cropped-thumb-2.jpg','cropped-thumb-2.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-thumb-2-jpg','','','2018-02-26 23:11:57','2018-02-26 23:11:57','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/cropped-thumb-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(329,1,'2018-03-06 00:48:10','2018-03-06 00:48:10','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y3h7-ONk4Xc\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y3h7-ONk4Xc\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Just got home from Austin and finished up the edit for this week. I riff a bit about meeting online friends IRL, my frustrations with California, and some of the clues we found around our Airbnb...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I didn\'t add it to the vlog, but all of us there from the Beaver Builder team filmed an \"Ask Us Anything\" AMA style video. I\'ve been successfully working more and more video content into my professional life—which makes the time put into learning all this much more fulfilling.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hope you enjoy. See you next week.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Sexually Ambiguous Cowboys and a Trip to Austin, Texas','','publish','open','open','','sexually-ambiguous-cowboys-and-a-trip-to-austin-texas','','','2018-03-06 00:48:10','2018-03-06 00:48:10','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=329',0,'post','',0),(331,1,'2018-03-06 00:48:50','2018-03-06 00:48:50','','austin-vlog','','inherit','open','closed','','austin-vlog','','','2018-03-06 00:48:50','2018-03-06 00:48:50','',329,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/austin-vlog.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(332,1,'2018-03-06 00:48:56','2018-03-06 00:48:56','','thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','thumb','','','2018-03-06 00:48:56','2018-03-06 00:48:56','',329,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(333,1,'2018-03-06 00:49:15','2018-03-06 00:49:15','http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-thumb.jpg','cropped-thumb.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-thumb-jpg','','','2018-03-06 00:49:15','2018-03-06 00:49:15','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(334,1,'2018-03-13 06:09:50','2018-03-13 06:09:50','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9_oRcPNr3g0\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9_oRcPNr3g0\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This week\'s vlog covers a lot of range. I really hope it doesn\'t come off too ranty.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I got some sweet footage of a bald eagle out at the Lexington Reservoir in Los Gatos.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pliny the Younger was just released, and I got the opportunity to try this year\'s batch.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I talk about taxes and traffic and go out to catch some red-light cheaters. Hey, California, let\'s work on enforcing the rules we have instead of creating new ones! Stop taxing the people who are playing by the rules and start asking the cheaters to pay more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How to Fold a Fitted Sheet + Bald Eagles, Beer, Traffic, & Taxes','','publish','open','open','','how-to-fold-a-fitted-sheet-bald-eagles-beer-traffic-taxes','','','2018-03-13 06:09:50','2018-03-13 06:09:50','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=334',0,'post','',1),(335,1,'2018-03-13 06:09:31','2018-03-13 06:09:31','','blog-thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','blog-thumb','','','2018-03-13 06:09:31','2018-03-13 06:09:31','',334,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/blog-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(337,1,'2018-03-13 06:10:26','2018-03-13 06:10:26','','vlog-thumb2','','inherit','open','closed','','vlog-thumb2','','','2018-03-13 06:10:26','2018-03-13 06:10:26','',334,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/vlog-thumb2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(338,1,'2018-03-13 06:10:46','2018-03-13 06:10:46','http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-vlog-thumb2.jpg','cropped-vlog-thumb2.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-vlog-thumb2-jpg','','','2018-03-13 06:10:46','2018-03-13 06:10:46','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-vlog-thumb2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(340,1,'2018-03-21 21:35:32','2018-03-21 21:35:32','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bWENVLAoddc\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bWENVLAoddc\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My original thinking was that I would come out to WordCamp Miami 2018 a bit early and have a relaxing beach to set up and do some work.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I had no idea my trip was smack in the middle of spring break. This trip brought me back to 90s MTV spring break specials. One of my favorite overheard quotes was, \"I\'ve never seen more bare asses in my life.\" It\'s true!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Miami was a beautiful city. Great people. Great food. Lots of new flavors, sights, and sounds. In part one, I am covering the \"work-cation\" part of the trip. Next week, I am going to share my time at WordCamp.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Miami — South Beach Spring Break MADNESS!','','publish','open','open','','miami-south-beach-spring-break-madness','','','2018-03-21 21:35:32','2018-03-21 21:35:32','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=340',0,'post','',2),(342,1,'2018-03-21 21:11:55','2018-03-21 21:11:55','','thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','thumb-3','','','2018-03-21 21:11:55','2018-03-21 21:11:55','',340,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/thumb-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(343,1,'2018-03-21 21:12:13','2018-03-21 21:12:13','http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-thumb-1.jpg','cropped-thumb-1.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-thumb-1-jpg','','','2018-03-21 21:12:13','2018-03-21 21:12:13','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-thumb-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(345,1,'2018-03-21 21:14:49','2018-03-21 21:14:49','','miami-2','','inherit','open','closed','','miami-2','','','2018-03-21 21:14:49','2018-03-21 21:14:49','',340,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/miami-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(346,1,'2018-03-21 21:23:37','2018-03-21 21:23:37','','wordcamp-miami-vlog','','inherit','open','closed','','wordcamp-miami-vlog','','','2018-03-21 21:23:37','2018-03-21 21:23:37','',340,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordcamp-miami-vlog.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(348,1,'2018-03-28 22:37:00','2018-03-28 22:37:00','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kxs4qCJN3MA\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kxs4qCJN3MA\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My Miami adventure continues with the work portion of the trip. WordCamp Miami 2018 was a blast. Over 1000 people attended the event. The weather was phenomenal. The team of volunteers that organized the camp did an amazing job. Thanks, guys.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once I finally peeled myself away from the beach, I went on a few adventures into town. I saw some old friends and made some new ones. Smoked a cigar and had an all-around excellent time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I can definitely see making WordCamp Miami one of my annuals. I am still kicking myself for the crummy focus job on the Chicago sunset timelapse, but I have a feeling I will redeem myself next week...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Miami Part 2 - WordCamp Miami 2018','','publish','open','open','','miami-part-2-wordcamp-miami-2018','','','2018-03-28 22:37:00','2018-03-28 22:37:00','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=348',0,'post','',0),(350,1,'2018-03-28 22:27:30','2018-03-28 22:27:30','','wordcamp-miami-vlog-2','','inherit','open','closed','','wordcamp-miami-vlog-2','','','2018-03-28 22:27:30','2018-03-28 22:27:30','',348,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordcamp-miami-vlog-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(351,1,'2018-03-28 22:30:12','2018-03-28 22:30:12','','wordcamp-miami-thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','wordcamp-miami-thumb','','','2018-03-28 22:30:12','2018-03-28 22:30:12','',348,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordcamp-miami-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(352,1,'2018-03-28 22:30:19','2018-03-28 22:30:19','http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-wordcamp-miami-thumb.jpg','cropped-wordcamp-miami-thumb.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-wordcamp-miami-thumb-jpg','','','2018-03-28 22:30:19','2018-03-28 22:30:19','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-wordcamp-miami-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(359,1,'2018-04-04 23:14:16','2018-04-04 23:14:16','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/-W3zA3QF_qA\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/-W3zA3QF_qA\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Boise was on my travel bucket list for the last year and I FINALLY made it out there. It was a super spontaneous, last-minute trip. I bought a one-way ticket ~12 hours before take off and I am so glad I did!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Treefort Music Fest was awesome! I saw George Clinton and I saw a TON of bands and music that I hadn\'t heard of before.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The food was great. The tech portion of the festival was fun. The beer was cold. The music was epic. I got to see it snow and wear shorts+tshirt on the same weekend. Not too shabby, Boise. Not too shabby at all!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Oh, and everyone I met out there was SO nice. You guys are beautiful.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Is Boise the BEST city EVER - Treefort Music Fest 2018','','publish','open','open','','is-boise-the-best-city-ever-treefort-music-fest-2018','','','2018-04-04 23:14:16','2018-04-04 23:14:16','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=359',0,'post','',0),(360,1,'2018-04-04 23:09:58','2018-04-04 23:09:58','','boise-treefort-blog-image','','inherit','open','closed','','boise-treefort-blog-image','','','2018-04-04 23:09:58','2018-04-04 23:09:58','',359,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/boise-treefort-blog-image.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(361,1,'2018-04-04 23:10:00','2018-04-04 23:10:00','','thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','thumb-4','','','2018-04-04 23:10:00','2018-04-04 23:10:00','',359,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(363,1,'2018-04-04 23:13:28','2018-04-04 23:13:28','http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/cropped-thumb.jpg','cropped-thumb.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-thumb-jpg-2','','','2018-04-04 23:13:28','2018-04-04 23:13:28','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/cropped-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(365,1,'2018-04-12 23:00:52','2018-04-12 23:00:52','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=boM-iYS0uDI\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=boM-iYS0uDI\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This week, I was totally focused on packing and prepping for my London/Iceland trip so the vlog isn\'t quite as action-packed as normal. I found a song that I really like about the springtime, so I did a spring-themed day and went fishing and droning. I wanted to get warmed up with the drone since I am taking it to Iceland.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It was going to be a REALLY slow week for the vlog, but then my plane got delayed for hours in LA. I took an impromptu beach visit, went swimming, then finished up the edit for this week on the plane!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I might be off a day or two on my posting days, but I should have a London and an Iceland vlog out over the next few weeks. Wish me luck!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Flying drones and catching fish - Enjoying the California spring','','publish','open','open','','flying-drones-and-catching-fish-enjoying-the-california-spring','','','2018-04-12 23:00:52','2018-04-12 23:00:52','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=365',0,'post','',0),(366,1,'2018-04-12 15:33:10','2018-04-12 15:33:10','','thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','thumb-5','','','2018-04-12 15:33:10','2018-04-12 15:33:10','',365,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/thumb-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(367,1,'2018-04-12 15:33:14','2018-04-12 15:33:14','','fishing-blog-thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','fishing-blog-thumb','','','2018-04-12 15:33:14','2018-04-12 15:33:14','',365,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/fishing-blog-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(368,1,'2018-04-12 15:33:56','2018-04-12 15:33:56','http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/cropped-thumb-1.jpg','cropped-thumb-1.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-thumb-1-jpg-2','','','2018-04-12 15:33:56','2018-04-12 15:33:56','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/cropped-thumb-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(372,1,'2018-04-28 16:04:57','2018-04-28 16:04:57','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/Ik06h8tE8hU\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/Ik06h8tE8hU\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I missed two weeks of posting vlogs, but I am back! I didn\'t want to spend any of my travel time editing. Sorry.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For this week, Justin and I hit London for some sightseeing adventures and WordCamp London. We explored on the tube, had a few nice dinners, took a ride on the London Eye, ate black pudding, and capped it all off with a solid visit to WordCamp London where we got to meet a bunch of the U.K.-based Beaver Builder crew.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As my good friend once said, there\'s nothing quite like partying hard with new friends in a new country and we had ample opportunity for that. Cheers, London! You sure showed a couple of Yankee wankers a proper time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','London -  Eating Blood and WordCamp London','','publish','open','open','','london-eating-blood-and-wordcamp-london','','','2018-04-28 16:04:57','2018-04-28 16:04:57','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=372',0,'post','',2),(373,1,'2018-04-28 16:04:05','2018-04-28 16:04:05','','london vlog thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','london-vlog-thumb','','','2018-04-28 16:04:05','2018-04-28 16:04:05','',372,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/london-vlog-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(374,1,'2018-04-28 16:04:12','2018-04-28 16:04:12','http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/cropped-london-vlog-thumb.jpg','cropped-london-vlog-thumb.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-london-vlog-thumb-jpg','','','2018-04-28 16:04:12','2018-04-28 16:04:12','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/cropped-london-vlog-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(375,1,'2018-04-28 16:04:22','2018-04-28 16:04:22','','london-blog-thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','london-blog-thumb','','','2018-04-28 16:04:22','2018-04-28 16:04:22','',372,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/london-blog-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(379,1,'2018-05-05 18:58:08','2018-05-05 18:58:08','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/9zAW3ZCkTyg\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/9zAW3ZCkTyg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My European adventure continues this week in the land of ice!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I stocked up on party supplies in the airport. Meet my roommate. We go on an epic adventure to see the edge of the North American tectonic plate, geysers, waterfalls, cows, a secret lagoon (it wasn\'t very secret afterall), and craters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On day 2, we all load up into a bus and drive it straight into a river. What could go wrong, right?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Iceland Part 1 - Chasing Waterfalls and Driving into Rivers','','publish','open','open','','iceland-part-1-chasing-waterfalls-and-driving-into-rivers','','','2018-05-05 18:58:08','2018-05-05 18:58:08','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=379',0,'post','',0),(381,1,'2018-05-05 18:57:20','2018-05-05 18:57:20','','iceland-vlog-featured-image','','inherit','open','closed','','iceland-vlog-featured-image','','','2018-05-05 18:57:20','2018-05-05 18:57:20','',379,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/iceland-vlog-featured-image.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(382,1,'2018-05-05 18:57:31','2018-05-05 18:57:31','','iceland-1-vlog-thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','iceland-1-vlog-thumb','','','2018-05-05 18:57:31','2018-05-05 18:57:31','',379,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/iceland-1-vlog-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(383,1,'2018-05-05 18:57:40','2018-05-05 18:57:40','http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/cropped-iceland-1-vlog-thumb.jpg','cropped-iceland-1-vlog-thumb.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-iceland-1-vlog-thumb-jpg','','','2018-05-05 18:57:40','2018-05-05 18:57:40','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/cropped-iceland-1-vlog-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(386,1,'2018-05-14 03:48:33','2018-05-14 03:48:33','<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a55pR1L5A8k\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a55pR1L5A8k\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you like watching people hiking, you\'re going to love this one! Our Iceland trip continues at the Volcano Huts. We climb mountains and built a solid bonfire. We drank coffee and ate some amazing food.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I did a lot of filming out there, so I am going to do a 3rd Iceland video eventually. This one is really all about the Geek Adventures trip. Somewhat related: I have been listening to a bunch of Icelandic music recently for the vlog and they make some really good tunes out there.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks a ton to everyone that came out and made this trip so much fun! :)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Thórsmörk Volcano Huts - Iceland part 2','','publish','open','open','','thorsmork-volcano-huts-iceland-part-2','','','2018-05-14 03:48:33','2018-05-14 03:48:33','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=386',0,'post','',0),(387,1,'2018-05-14 03:38:17','2018-05-14 03:38:17','','iceland-2-blog-thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','iceland-2-blog-thumb','','','2018-05-14 03:38:17','2018-05-14 03:38:17','',386,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/iceland-2-blog-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(388,1,'2018-05-14 03:38:28','2018-05-14 03:38:28','','vlog-15-thumb','','inherit','open','closed','','vlog-15-thumb','','','2018-05-14 03:38:28','2018-05-14 03:38:28','',386,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/vlog-15-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(389,1,'2018-05-14 03:46:30','2018-05-14 03:46:30','http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/cropped-vlog-15-thumb.jpg','cropped-vlog-15-thumb.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-vlog-15-thumb-jpg','','','2018-05-14 03:46:30','2018-05-14 03:46:30','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/cropped-vlog-15-thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(392,1,'2018-12-06 04:20:28','2018-12-06 04:20:28','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>November 9th-13th, 2018</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During early 2018, I was experimenting with video production and vlogging. I think the proliferation of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9Xc7DN-noAc&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=344\">video as a communication medium is drastically changing the world</a>, and my goal was to learn more about the video medium, editing, and filming. I had a blast doing this, but producing a weekly vlog was <em>very</em> time consuming and I eventually reached a bit of a learning plateau.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of my favorite parts about vlogging was the opportunity to document memories and adventures from my travels. I\'m hoping to continue this via a different medium, long-form, multimedia-rich&nbsp;blogging and journaling...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Flying over California, through a thick haze, one day after the Camp Fire begins</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Two days before leaving on this trip, a high fire danger warning starting making rounds through my neighborhood Facebook group. California had yet to see any significant rainfall and strong winds coupled with low humidity were in the forecast.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Early the next day, a friend from Northern California posted a foreboding message about a fast-moving&nbsp;wildfire kicking up in the mountains near Chico. Sure enough, it ended up being the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camp_Fire_(2018)\">Camp Fire</a> which ravaged the town of Paradise, killing dozens and leaving a trail of ashes in it\'s wake of destruction.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[419,417,418,438],\"columns\":3,\"linkTo\":\"media\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><a href=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/smoke1-1024x762.jpg\"><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/smoke1-1024x762.jpg\" alt=\"Smoke from the Camp Fire over California.\" data-id=\"419\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island/smoke1/\" class=\"wp-image-419\"/></a></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><a href=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/smoke3-1024x762.jpg\"><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/smoke3-1024x762.jpg\" alt=\"Smoke from the Camp Fire over California.\" data-id=\"417\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island/smoke3/\" class=\"wp-image-417\"/></a></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><a href=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/smoke2-1-1024x762.jpg\"><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/smoke2-1-1024x762.jpg\" alt=\"Smoke from the Camp Fire over California.\" data-id=\"418\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island/smoke2-2/\" class=\"wp-image-418\"/></a></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><a href=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/campfire-smoke-bay-area-2018-1024x949.jpg\"><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/campfire-smoke-bay-area-2018-1024x949.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"438\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island/campfire-smoke-bay-area-2018/\" class=\"wp-image-438\"/></a></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Roughly twenty-four hours later, I boarded a plane and flew over what would become the most deadly and devastating&nbsp;fire in California history. Flying over the Camp Fire smoke was like rubbernecking a car wreck on the highway. I couldn\'t take my eyes away from the window and the apocalyptic haze blanketing the upper half of my home state. I\'d be lying if I said I didn\'t recognize this as a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to witness, from above, the sheer magnitude of nature\'s most destructive element.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Eating around Seattle Washington &amp; Pike Place Market </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>TL;DR: Radiator Whiskey, Jack\'s Fish Spot, and Pasta Casalinga were my \"would go again\" spots for food and drink.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I\'d never been to Seattle and it was near the top of my US city bucket list. I was excited about fresh seafood, clear weather, and the opportunity to see a few good friends from the area. After ditching my bag at the hotel, I walked over to Pike Place Market for some grub. I had a chowder craving and was directed towards <a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/ofDpDu6kQhy\">Pike Place Chowder</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I laughed under my breath as I followed the novelty-long line, trying to make my way to the end. When I finally found it, I noticed <a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/usByPrFqCBn\">Jack\'s Fish Spot</a> across the way with some fantastic looking live Dungeness crabs out front. I opted to grab a chowder at and it was choice!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p><strong>Pro Tip</strong>: Skip the line at Pike Place Chowder and pop by Jack\'s Fish Spot instead.</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I kept exploring the market. It was teeming with tourists and locals alike. All sorts of sights and smells. There was a spectacular florist and many people were carrying lovely flower bouquets. I grabbed a pasta dish at <a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/yp8PjwSAvbK2\">Pasta Casalinga</a> and a spirit-forward whiskey cocktail at <a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/3QEw3ovWhoR2\">Radiator Whiskey</a>. I\'d highly recommend anyone to do the same.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>WordCamp Seattle 2018</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I used to poke fun at people who went to lots of WordCamps. I\'d joke about how they got any work done; now I am one of those people. At the time, I didn\'t realize how isolating remote work can be. Camps are an opportunity to get out from behind the computer screen and meet with the people we interact with daily face-to-face.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://2018.seattle.wordcamp.org/\">WordCamp Seattle</a> was an amazing camp thanks, no doubt, to the stellar organizing team, volunteers, speakers, and everyone that attended. I spent most of my time in the \"hallway track\" chit-chatting, but I did manage to squeeze in a few sessions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of my favorites was Chris Tiezel\'s session about data responsibility. The talk was about the responsibility developers have to consider unintended consequences of their work. One example explained how the fitness tracking application, Strava, accidentally disclosed the location of a secret military base in the Middle East due to base personnel using Strava and their data subsequently being published on <a href=\"https://www.strava.com/heatmap\">Strava\'s Global Heatmap</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My new favorite WordCamp story happened after a slightly-rowdy group dinner. We were at an Italian restaurant on a third floor. On our way out, we saw, through a window, flashing lights and tons of people dancing in the building across the way. It looked like a perfect \"next spot\" for our group to keep the party going.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We made our way over and discovered the party was happening on the third floor of a hotel. I know how to play the game, but I\'ve never been good at sneaking into places. Not knowing how to make our way from the lobby to the party upstairs, I walked into the hotel lobby like I owned the place, casually walked up to the concierge and said something this...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[611,612,610],\"columns\":2} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/robby-michelle-1024x682.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"611\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island/robby-michelle/\" class=\"wp-image-611\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/robby-cami.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"612\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island/robby-cami/\" class=\"wp-image-612\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/robby-mendel-1-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"610\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island/robby-mendel-2/\" class=\"wp-image-610\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"Hi there. We met some new friends at the bar earlier and they mentioned they were hosting a party here. We didn\'t catch their name, but they invited us to join them and I was wondering if you could please point us in the right direction?\"</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The woman gave me a long and suspicious look. With a raised&nbsp;eyebrow, she informed me that the only \"party\" happening that evening was a high school dance. Whoops! I quickly told her we must have the wrong place and gave the \"abort mission\" gesture to the rest of the group. We scurried outside, laughed, and looked back up towards the \"party\" to see, sure enough, they were all teenagers! We decided to call it an evening and go our separate ways, but, around this time, we noticed we were missing one from our group.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We did our best to find our friend, but we couldn\'t contact him. His colleague assured us he would be okay, so we left it at that. The next day, we found out he had snuck off to the use the restroom in the hotel lobby. He came out to find we were all gone and assumed we\'d gone upstairs. Naturally, he made his way up to the party and did a few dances before he realized we weren\'t there and he was the oldest person in the room beside a few chaperones.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2> An epic Airbnb in Anacortes &amp; San Juan Islands </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The next stop on my itinerary was a visit with my grandparents who live on an island in the San Juan Island chain. I decided to stay on the mainland in Anacortes, then wake up early and take a ferry out for a day trip to the island.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The drive from Seattle to Anacortes took about two hours and I stopped by <a href=\"https://parks.state.wa.us/497/Deception-Pass\">Deception Pass State Park</a> on the way up. I was hoping to find some hiking, but Deception Pass was more of a drive-through, enjoy-the-view sort of park.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[458,457]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-2-1024x639.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"458\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-2018-san-juan-island/anacortes-2/\" class=\"wp-image-458\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-1-1024x639.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"457\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-2018-san-juan-island/anacortes-1/\" class=\"wp-image-457\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My Grandma warned me that Anacortes wasn\'t her favorite place to spend a night, so I didn\'t expect to find anything spectacular in terms of motels and lodging. As I was browsing Airbnb, I found a <a href=\"https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/13748265\">stunning in-law cottage on a bluff directly above the Pacific Ocean</a>. Not only did the view look amazing, but the price was right also!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What I found when I got there was by far and away the nicest Airbnb I\'ve ever stayed at. The view of the ocean and the islands were far better than the pictures led on. The cottage was quaint and tastefully furnished. The host even left a plate of fresh-baked goodies for me to enjoy during my stay. I arrived right before the sunset and took some pictures of hummingbirds dancing around a feeder with a west coast ocean sunset in the background.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[459,606,460],\"columns\":2,\"linkTo\":\"media\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><a href=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-3-1024x639.jpg\"><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-3-1024x639.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"459\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island/anacortes-3/\" class=\"wp-image-459\"/></a></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><a href=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1114-1024x1024.jpeg\"><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1114-1024x1024.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"606\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island/img_1114/\" class=\"wp-image-606\"/></a></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><a href=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-4-1024x639.jpg\"><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-4-1024x639.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"460\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island/anacortes-4/\" class=\"wp-image-460\"/></a></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That evening, I found a seafood restaurant and went to check out the local dive bar scene. I wasn\'t disappointed. I wound up at the <a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/xyXBca1StoG2\">Brown Lantern Ale House</a> for a few pints, then went in for an early night so I could wake up the next day.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The last time I\'d been on San Juan Island I was eight years old. At that age, I wasn\'t allowed to roam around without supervision but, because it was a small town on an island, I had free reign to go wherever I pleased. The only rule I was to follow was to stay out of the ocean...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I quickly made friends with a few local kids. We were playing around on the beach and found a huge piece of styrofoam that presumably drifted in from the ocean. The styrofoam was shaped like a raft and it certainly appeared seaworthy. Naturally, I launched the vessel out for her maiden voyage into the surf. As it turned out, it was <em>not</em> seaworthy. It quickly capsized and I wound up in the one place I wasn\'t supposed to be, the ocean. My grandparents were not amused.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Visiting them 20 years later was a much different experience. I rode the ferry on to the island and was greeted with beautiful weather and my grandpa waiting to pick me up. Apart from the great company, the highlights of the visit were culinary. We popped into the San Juan Brewery for lunch and a drink. Two thumbs up! Later, my Grandma, who is a phenomenal cook, put together a fantastic dinner of Dungeness Crab and salad.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My last stop in Washington was back in Seattle where I met with a good friend and fellow traveler for lunch. She is an avid backpacker, climber, and outdoors-woman and I always enjoy hearing tales of her adventures. After a Cubano sandwich and some story trading, I headed back to the airport to continue to the next leg of my journey, Alaska!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','WordCamp Seattle, Pike Place Market, &  San Juan Island','During early November 2018, I flew over massive amounts of smoke from the Camp Fire en route to Washington. I had the opportunity to eat my way through Seattle and Pike Place Market, then drove north to Anacortes where I stayed in one of my favorite Airbnbs of all times. From there, I jumped on a ferry to San Juan Island to visit my grandparents.','publish','open','open','','wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island','','','2018-12-06 04:20:28','2018-12-06 04:20:28','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough//?p=392',0,'post','',0),(417,1,'2018-11-29 01:44:40','2018-11-29 01:44:40','','smoke3','','inherit','open','closed','','smoke3','','','2018-11-29 01:44:40','2018-11-29 01:44:40','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/smoke3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(418,1,'2018-11-29 01:44:41','2018-11-29 01:44:41','','smoke2','','inherit','open','closed','','smoke2-2','','','2018-11-29 01:44:41','2018-11-29 01:44:41','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/smoke2-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(419,1,'2018-11-29 01:44:43','2018-11-29 01:44:43','','smoke1','','inherit','open','closed','','smoke1','','','2018-11-29 01:44:43','2018-11-29 01:44:43','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/smoke1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(431,1,'2018-12-01 00:32:07','2018-12-01 00:32:07','','womp-2','','inherit','open','closed','','womp-2','','','2018-12-01 00:32:07','2018-12-01 00:32:07','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/womp-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(438,1,'2018-12-01 04:00:53','2018-12-01 04:00:53','','campfire-smoke-bay-area-2018','','inherit','open','closed','','campfire-smoke-bay-area-2018','','','2018-12-01 04:00:53','2018-12-01 04:00:53','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/campfire-smoke-bay-area-2018.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(446,1,'2018-12-01 06:20:08','2018-12-01 06:20:08','','Anacortes Sunset TL','','inherit','open','closed','','anacortes-sunset-tl','','','2018-12-01 06:20:08','2018-12-01 06:20:08','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Anacortes-Sunset-TL.mp4',0,'attachment','video/mp4',0),(457,1,'2018-12-02 06:13:34','2018-12-02 06:13:34','','anacortes-1','','inherit','open','closed','','anacortes-1','','','2018-12-02 06:13:34','2018-12-02 06:13:34','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(458,1,'2018-12-02 06:13:36','2018-12-02 06:13:36','','anacortes-2','','inherit','open','closed','','anacortes-2','','','2018-12-02 06:13:36','2018-12-02 06:13:36','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(459,1,'2018-12-02 06:13:39','2018-12-02 06:13:39','','anacortes-3','','inherit','open','closed','','anacortes-3','','','2018-12-02 06:13:39','2018-12-02 06:13:39','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(460,1,'2018-12-02 06:13:41','2018-12-02 06:13:41','','anacortes-4','','inherit','open','closed','','anacortes-4','','','2018-12-02 06:13:41','2018-12-02 06:13:41','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(461,1,'2018-12-02 06:13:44','2018-12-02 06:13:44','','anacortes-5','','inherit','open','closed','','anacortes-5','','','2018-12-02 06:13:44','2018-12-02 06:13:44','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-5.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(470,1,'2018-12-06 04:30:37','2018-12-06 04:30:37','','smoke4','','inherit','open','closed','','smoke4','','','2018-12-06 04:30:37','2018-12-06 04:30:37','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/smoke4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(472,1,'2018-12-06 04:41:48','2018-12-06 04:41:48','','robby-mendel','','inherit','open','closed','','robby-mendel','','','2018-12-06 04:41:48','2018-12-06 04:41:48','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/robby-mendel.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(476,1,'2018-12-06 05:03:51','2018-12-06 05:03:51','','anacortes-360-bg','','inherit','open','closed','','anacortes-360-bg','','','2018-12-06 05:03:51','2018-12-06 05:03:51','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/anacortes-360-bg.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(507,1,'2018-12-28 06:37:41','2018-12-28 06:37:41','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After countless grueling trips up fifty-five stairs, lugging boxes and gear, I\'m completely moved out of my cottage. It\'s bittersweet.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For the last five years, I\'ve lived and worked from a spectacularly beautiful spot in the Santa Cruz Mountains with a sweeping view of the Lexington Reservoir. I\'ve been immersed in nature and regularly watched the deer, turkeys, bald eagles, foxes, coyotes, bobcats, beavers, snakes, and all sorts of other critters from my windows. I could walk out the door and be steps away from fishing, hiking, and mountain biking. Stumbling on that little lakeside cottage was one of the luckiest moments of my life, but it\'s time to say goodbye.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With windows and doors wide open it was <em>maybe</em> 350 square feet, and I managed to utilize every nook and corner. I had HDMI, Ethernet, TRS, power, and various other cables neatly snaking through, all well-managed and more-or-less hidden from sight. I had some amazing and arguably tasteful artwork that was given to me and created by my great friends on display. I had a full-fledged media studio capable of producing just about any sort of digital content imaginable. I had a \"dining\" table that served as a staging ground for fishing, biking, camping, camera, and festie gear.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It was the best of both worlds. A quiet and peaceful mountain cottage, with blazing fast internet and connectivity, that was only 10 minutes from bougie restaurants and civilization. It was a damn good home.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[555,556,557,558,559,560,561]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_0316-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"555\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/beginning-my-new-life-as-a-digital-nomad/img_0316/\" class=\"wp-image-555\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_0503-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"556\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/beginning-my-new-life-as-a-digital-nomad/img_0503/\" class=\"wp-image-556\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1216-1024x743.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"557\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/beginning-my-new-life-as-a-digital-nomad/img_1216/\" class=\"wp-image-557\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1577-1024x809.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"558\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/beginning-my-new-life-as-a-digital-nomad/img_1577/\" class=\"wp-image-558\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1615-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"559\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/beginning-my-new-life-as-a-digital-nomad/img_1615/\" class=\"wp-image-559\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1639-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"560\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/beginning-my-new-life-as-a-digital-nomad/img_1639/\" class=\"wp-image-560\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1987-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"561\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/beginning-my-new-life-as-a-digital-nomad/img_1987/\" class=\"wp-image-561\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I heard something recently about the importance of one\'s room or workspace. Building and designing a room forces you to think about the purpose of that room. I lived <em>and worked</em> from my \"room\" and put a tremendous amount of thought and care into dialing it in to near perfection. It was an ongoing existential exercise. What\'s important to me? How do I want to spend my life\'s time? What do I want to produce? What do I need close by to be the most satisfied, content, and productive with my life?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My plan for 2019 is to violently break out of that meticulously curated comfort zone. Thanks to the overwhelming generosity and flexibility of my family, I\'m now a proper boomerang millennial! They\'ve graciously cleared some space for me to store my gear at their house and I am planning to experiment with a nomadic existence in 2019 and beyond! Full-time traveling, both stateside and abroad.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I\'m in a bizarre and fortunate place right now where I have absolutely nothing connecting me to any particular spot on this planet. So to me, the logical thing to do to take advantage of that circumstance is to wander. I\'m hoping to spend a few weeks or months here and a few weeks or months there. I\'m almost definitely going to spend some time in Europe, SE Asia, Japan, and South America. I\'m hoping to visit India. I\'m thinking about an extended cross-country road trip around springtime. Maybe I\'ll do a tour! The only definitive plan right now is rambling.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, if you need a travel buddy let me know where in the world to find you and I\'ll do my best to be there! Thanks to everyone that inspired this life change and helped make it a reality. Goodbye, house. Thanks for all the good times.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>/chapter</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','One chapter ends and a new one begins. A eulogy to my home in the Santa Cruz Mountains.','For the last five years, I\'ve lived and worked from a spectacularly beautiful spot in the Santa Cruz Mountains with a sweeping view of the Lexington Reservoir. I\'ve been immersed in nature and regularly watched the deer, turkeys, bald eagles, foxes, coyotes, bobcats, beavers, snakes, and all sorts of other critters from my windows. I could walk out the door and be steps away from fishing, hiking, and mountain biking. Stumbling on that little lakeside cottage was one of the luckiest moments of my life, but it\'s time to say goodbye.','publish','open','open','','one-chapter-ends-and-a-new-one-begins-a-eulogy-to-my-home-in-the-santa-cruz-mountains','','','2018-12-28 06:37:41','2018-12-28 06:37:41','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough/?p=507',0,'post','',0),(520,1,'2018-12-28 23:00:23','2018-12-28 23:00:23','','robbymccullough','','inherit','open','closed','','robbymccullough','','','2018-12-28 23:00:23','2018-12-28 23:00:23','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/robbymccullough.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(522,1,'2018-12-28 23:18:19','2018-12-28 23:18:19','','Default','','publish','closed','closed','','default-2','','','2018-12-28 23:18:19','2018-12-28 23:18:19','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough/default/',0,'advgb_profiles','',0),(531,1,'2018-12-28 23:53:26','2018-12-28 23:53:26','','digital-nomad-featured-image','','inherit','open','closed','','digital-nomad-featured-image','','','2018-12-28 23:53:26','2018-12-28 23:53:26','',507,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/digital-nomad-featured-image.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(555,1,'2018-12-30 06:42:57','2018-12-30 06:42:57','','IMG_0316','','inherit','open','closed','','img_0316','','','2018-12-30 06:42:57','2018-12-30 06:42:57','',507,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_0316.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(556,1,'2018-12-30 06:43:00','2018-12-30 06:43:00','','IMG_0503','','inherit','open','closed','','img_0503','','','2018-12-30 06:43:00','2018-12-30 06:43:00','',507,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_0503.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(557,1,'2018-12-30 06:43:02','2018-12-30 06:43:02','','IMG_1216','','inherit','open','closed','','img_1216','','','2018-12-30 06:43:02','2018-12-30 06:43:02','',507,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1216.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(558,1,'2018-12-30 06:43:05','2018-12-30 06:43:05','','IMG_1577','','inherit','open','closed','','img_1577','','','2018-12-30 06:43:05','2018-12-30 06:43:05','',507,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1577.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(559,1,'2018-12-30 06:43:07','2018-12-30 06:43:07','','IMG_1615','','inherit','open','closed','','img_1615','','','2018-12-30 06:43:07','2018-12-30 06:43:07','',507,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1615.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(560,1,'2018-12-30 06:43:10','2018-12-30 06:43:10','','IMG_1639','','inherit','open','closed','','img_1639','','','2018-12-30 06:43:10','2018-12-30 06:43:10','',507,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1639.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(561,1,'2018-12-30 06:43:11','2018-12-30 06:43:11','','IMG_1987','','inherit','open','closed','','img_1987','','','2018-12-30 06:43:11','2018-12-30 06:43:11','',507,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1987.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(606,1,'2018-12-30 19:09:54','2018-12-30 19:09:54','','IMG_1114','','inherit','open','closed','','img_1114','','','2018-12-30 19:09:54','2018-12-30 19:09:54','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/IMG_1114.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(610,1,'2018-12-30 19:23:57','2018-12-30 19:23:57','','robby-mendel','','inherit','open','closed','','robby-mendel-2','','','2018-12-30 19:23:57','2018-12-30 19:23:57','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/robby-mendel-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(611,1,'2018-12-30 19:24:01','2018-12-30 19:24:01','','robby-michelle','','inherit','open','closed','','robby-michelle','','','2018-12-30 19:24:01','2018-12-30 19:24:01','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/robby-michelle.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(612,1,'2018-12-30 19:24:05','2018-12-30 19:24:05','','robby-cami','','inherit','open','closed','','robby-cami','','','2018-12-30 19:24:05','2018-12-30 19:24:05','',392,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/robby-cami.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(619,1,'2019-01-06 03:46:08','2019-01-06 03:46:08','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>November 13th-19th, 2018</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After <a href=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/wordcamp-seattle-pike-place-market-san-juan-island/\">spending a few days exploring Washington State,</a> I continued north to Fairbanks, Alaska. I\'m a native Californian and, prior to this trip, could count on one hand the number of times I\'d seen it snowing. Visiting Alaska was a chance to break out of my temperature comfort zone, learn how to drive in the snow, and experience the Alaskan culture and landscape which was lauded as totally unique to the lower 48\'s. I was excited to explore in Alaska, but my biggest motivator for the trip was a chance to see the Northern Lights!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Earlier in the year, I visited Iceland and, while in the right location, didn\'t get a chance to see any aurora activity. After being so close and missing, it decided I would have to make another attempt as soon as I could.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Preparations</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I go back and forth between over-preparing and winging it when it comes to travel. For this trip, I did a fair amount of research and planning ahead of time. I wanted to stay somewhere slightly outside of the city so I could avoid light pollution and see the Northern Lights from where I stayed. That meant I needed to rent an AWD vehicle as opposed to relying on taxis (Lyft/Uber were just starting to operate in Fairbanks at the time of writing this and not 100% reliable).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[636,638,637,639],\"columns\":3} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-1-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"636\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/?attachment_id=636\" class=\"wp-image-636\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-3-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"638\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/?attachment_id=638\" class=\"wp-image-638\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-2-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"637\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/?attachment_id=637\" class=\"wp-image-637\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-4-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"639\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/?attachment_id=639\" class=\"wp-image-639\"/><figcaption>Shots from the front yard of my Airbnb</figcaption></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I joined and started following a <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/5337433675/\">Fairbanks, Alaska Facebook group</a> and <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/fairbanks\">subreddit</a>. Lots of potential travelers have posted questions, so there was a wealth of helpful information. I rented a vehicle through one of the airport-based rental companies and I grabbed an Airbnb that was a few miles outside of town. In hindsight, I would have tried to find an Airbnb that was on the other side of the ridge as I didn\'t have a great view of the northern horizon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Cold Weather Prep</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I\'ve been slowly accumulating cold-weather gear. I brought my <a href=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/go/merrell\">waterproof hiking shoes</a>, <a href=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/go/merino-socks\">warm wool socks</a>, a few long-sleeve base layers, a hoodie, scarf, <a href=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/go/puff-jacket\">synthetic down puff jacket</a>, and a beanie. I also added a set of long johns to the mix for this trip. It got as low as -6°F and I didn\'t have any trouble staying warm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Layering combined with really warm socks and a beanie+hood seemed to do the trick. Granted, I tend to run warm and, by Fairbanks standards, -6 isn\'t all that cold. If it were much colder, a pair of insulated boots and a more significant jacket probably would have been necessary.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>First time driving in snow</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I feel a little silly that, at 33 years old, I\'d never driven in snow before. It was a little bit nerve wracking at first but, once I got comfortable, it was actually pretty fun. There was about a half foot of snow on the ground when I got into town.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[626,627,628],\"columns\":2} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/ak-driving-1-1024x796.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"626\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/?attachment_id=626\" class=\"wp-image-626\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/ak-driving-2-1024x817.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"627\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/?attachment_id=627\" class=\"wp-image-627\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/ak-driving-3-1024x694.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"628\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/?attachment_id=628\" class=\"wp-image-628\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Driving in the actual snow was a lot easier than driving a few days later when the snow melted and the roads iced up. To be honest, it reminded me a lot of the ice levels in Mario Kart. Once I made that connection, things got a lot easier. Anticipate the slide and hope your wheels catch when they need to.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Moose meat</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I love tasting local flavors when I travel, so I did some research about Alaskan game meat. Restaurants can\'t serve \"wild\" meat like moose or bear, so I made a post in the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/5337433675/\">Fairbanks Facebook Group</a> offering to bring wine and snacks if any hunters wanted to invite me over for dinner. Unfortunately, there were no takers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a stroke of good luck, I was drinking and chatting with a few locals and mentioned I was scoping out the local dive bar scene. One of them suggested <a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/bkGSTB4yvnv\">The Mecca</a> which was a well-known hangout spot for Native Alaskans. I popped by and, again, got to chatting with a few of the regulars there. <em>They</em> suggested heading to the <a href=\"https://www.morristhompsoncenter.org/\">Morris Thompson Cultural and Visitors Center</a> where there was a Gwich’in Fiddle Dance and potluck!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the potluck, I got to try some moose stew and it was delicious! To be honest, the flavor of the meat was hard to distinguish from the rest of the stew, but it was a nice warm meal on a chilly evening and a check off the Alaskan experience list.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Chena Hot Springs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Just about everyone I talked to recommended making a visit out to <a href=\"https://chenahotsprings.com/\">Chena Hot Springs</a>. It\'s about 60 miles outside of town through some serene and gorgeous Alaskan wilderness. I was told to keep an eye peeled when driving over bridges as the creeks and rivers are like highways for all the wildlife. I was hoping to catch a glimpse of a moose or a bear, but alas I didn\'t see any. I did see several mushers with their dog teams, though!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The road to Chena was relatively straight and flat, well maintained, and frequently travelled, although I understand it can get very slick and treacherous during winter storms. After arriving I grabbed lunch and a brew at their restaurant. I bought a sticker to add to my collection and then went exploring. They offered dog sled tours, but I found it way more fun to visit with all the dogs in their kennels. It\'s a great spot for animal lovers—they also have reindeer! After playing with the pups, I took a little hike through the surrounding valley.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[644,645,646,647,648],\"columns\":3} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-1-1-1024x792.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"644\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/fairbanks-1-2/\" class=\"wp-image-644\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-2-1-1024x703.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"645\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/fairbanks-2-2/\" class=\"wp-image-645\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-3-1-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"646\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/fairbanks-3-2/\" class=\"wp-image-646\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-4-1-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"647\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/fairbanks-4-2/\" class=\"wp-image-647\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-5-1-1024x686.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"648\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/fairbanks-5-2/\" class=\"wp-image-648\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After an hour or so of hiking in the cold, I popped into the hot springs to warm up. It was a sensational experience! The springs were surrounded by colorful lights that illuminated the steam and made for a super peaceful experience. It was below freezing out, but I only noticed when my hair would freeze up from being out of the warm water for too long.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Alaskan History Museum</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sometimes I wish I were more interested in museums and culture and stuff like that. Checking out the history museum was a bit of a novelty for me, but I had a half day to kill and it was close by.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That said, it was pretty sweet! The building was totally photogenic and there were some really impressive exhibits. One stand out was the giant grizzly bear taxidermy! I didn\'t appreciate how big grizzly\'s could get until I got to walk up face to face with this one.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[664,665,666,663]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-6-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"664\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/fairbanks-6/\" class=\"wp-image-664\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-7-1024x684.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"665\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/fairbanks-7/\" class=\"wp-image-665\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-8-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"666\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/fairbanks-8/\" class=\"wp-image-666\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-5-2-1024x726.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"663\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/fairbanks-5-3/\" class=\"wp-image-663\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Another interesting one was <em><a href=\"https://www.uaf.edu/museum/exhibits/galleries/the-place-where-you-go-to/\">The Place Where you go to Listen</a></em>, a \"musical ecosystem [that] gives voice to the rhythms of daylight and darkness, the phases of the moon, the seismic vibrations of the earth, and the dance of the aurora borealis.\" Pretty psychedelic!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Northern Lights</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I was excited to visit Alaska for more reasons than just seeing the Northern Lights, but it was definitely #1 on my wish list. After staying up late each night and waking up early each morning, it was my last night in AK and my last chance at seeing the lights.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It was overcast the whole day, but there was a window of clear skies predicted from 2-4 am. The clouds were so thick I was skeptical it would happen. The aurora predictions weren\'t great either, but they were better than the previous two days; a 17% chance. The trip had been amazing and I wasn\'t discouraged that&nbsp;I hadn\'t seen the auroras, but I was already thinking about how and when to make another trek north.&nbsp;:)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[671,670,672],\"columns\":2} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/nn-1-3-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"671\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/nn-1-3/\" class=\"wp-image-671\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/nn-1-2-1024x688.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"670\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/nn-1-2/\" class=\"wp-image-670\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/nn-1-4-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"672\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/nn-1-4/\" class=\"wp-image-672\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I was sitting in the car reading a book, under a dome of thick clouds, and noticed a strange glow peeking through. I couldn\'t tell if it was just the sky or the moonlight shining through the clouds. I whipped out the camera, took a long exposure and, sure enough, it was green! I saw the lights! I was super jazzed at that point just to see a faint green glow poking through the haze.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Then, the clouds started to clear and the real show started up! I\'ve never seen anything like it. There were the most gorgeous natural gradients of all sorts of colors and a wild random dancing and fluttering of the lights.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[674,675,673],\"columns\":2} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/nn-1-6-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"674\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/nn-1-6/\" class=\"wp-image-674\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/nn-1-1024x707.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"675\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/nn-1/\" class=\"wp-image-675\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/nn-1-5-1024x646.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"673\" data-link=\"http://localhost/robbymccullough/visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis/nn-1-5/\" class=\"wp-image-673\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Two other tourists showed up and we got to share our overwhelming awe of what was going on around us. The peak lasted almost an hour. I was running around in 6 inches of snow all night and, by the end, I couldn\'t feel a single toe, but I was totally unbothered. I couldn\'t have asked for a better way to cap off this life-changing adventure!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Visiting Fairbanks, Alaska for the Aurora Borealis','','publish','open','open','','visiting-fairbanks-alaska-for-the-aurora-borealis','','','2019-01-06 03:46:08','2019-01-06 03:46:08','',0,'http://localhost/robbymccullough/?p=619',0,'post','',0),(626,1,'2019-01-06 01:13:36','2019-01-06 01:13:36','','ak-driving-1','','inherit','open','closed','','ak-driving-1','','','2019-01-06 01:13:36','2019-01-06 01:13:36','',619,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/ak-driving-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(627,1,'2019-01-06 01:13:39','2019-01-06 01:13:39','','ak-driving-2','','inherit','open','closed','','ak-driving-2','','','2019-01-06 01:13:39','2019-01-06 01:13:39','',619,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/ak-driving-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(628,1,'2019-01-06 01:13:42','2019-01-06 01:13:42','','ak-driving-3','','inherit','open','closed','','ak-driving-3','','','2019-01-06 01:13:42','2019-01-06 01:13:42','',619,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/ak-driving-3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(633,1,'2019-01-06 02:56:13','2019-01-06 02:56:13','','alaska-featured-image','','inherit','open','closed','','alaska-featured-image','','','2019-01-06 02:56:13','2019-01-06 02:56:13','',619,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/alaska-featured-image.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(635,1,'2019-01-06 03:05:47','2019-01-06 03:05:47','','alaska-featured-image-2','','inherit','open','closed','','alaska-featured-image-2','','','2019-01-06 03:05:47','2019-01-06 03:05:47','',619,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/alaska-featured-image-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(636,1,'2019-01-06 03:39:54','2019-01-06 03:39:54','','fairbanks-1','','inherit','open','closed','','fairbanks-1','','','2019-01-06 03:39:54','2019-01-06 03:39:54','',619,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(637,1,'2019-01-06 03:39:59','2019-01-06 03:39:59','','fairbanks-2','','inherit','open','closed','','fairbanks-2','','','2019-01-06 03:39:59','2019-01-06 03:39:59','',619,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fairbanks-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(638,1,'2019-01-09 21:07:11','2019-01-09 21:07:11','','Instagram','','publish','closed','closed','','instagram','','','2019-01-09 21:11:47','2019-01-09 21:11:47','',0,'http://localhost/robby-fresh/2019/01/09/instagram/',1,'nav_me